s home?\u201d I said, \u201cThe Prophet\u00a0was a man among men. He would remove fleas from his clothes, milk his sheep, and serve himself.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 26194 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Arna'ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36794,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/08\/11\/simple-life-of-the-prophet\/","url_meta":{"origin":896,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Zuhd: The simple living of the Prophet","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: She said to \u2018Urwah, \u201cO my nephew, we used to sight three crescent moons in two months without having any fire to cook in the house of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him.\u201d \u2018Urwah said, \u201cHow did you live?\u201d Aisha said, \u201cWith the two\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4288,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/05\/fajr-rakaat-light\/","url_meta":{"origin":896,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Fajr: The Prophet would sometimes pray lightly","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would sometimes perform two cycles of prayer before the dawn prayer so lightly that I would say to myself, \"Did he recite Surat al-Fatihah?\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1165, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 724 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon)\u00a0according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33026,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/01\/prophets-dua-ruku-sujud\/","url_meta":{"origin":896,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Salat: The Prophet&#8217;s supplication in bowing, prostration","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would say in his bowing and prostration, \u201cGlory be to you, Allah our Lord, and your praises. Forgive me.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 4042, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 484 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26126,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/03\/26\/masjid-women-leave-before-prophet\/","url_meta":{"origin":896,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Mosques: The Prophet lets women leave before himself","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 26, 2018","format":fal